        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 1<supplied reason="lost">3</supplied><ref n="1"
                                target="#Deut-013-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut013-P303v-L4_trl" n="4"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.012.trl.xml#Deut012-P303v-L4_trl" />
                        <l n="1">Every word I command you:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             you shall be watchful to do it. You shall not add to it or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             take away from it.</l>
                        <l n="2">If a prophet arises among you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             or a dreamer of dreams, and gives you a sign or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             a wonder,</l>
                        <l n="3">And the sign or wonder
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             of which he spoke to — saying, “Let us go after the service of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             other gods,” whom you have not known, “and let us serve
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             them,” — comes,</l>
                        <l n="4">You shall not listen to the words of that prophet or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             that dreamer of dreams, because the Lord your God is testing you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             to know whether you love the service of the Lord your God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             with all your heart and with all your soul.</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             You shall walk after the Lord your God’s order and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             fear him and keep his commandments and listen his voice,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and you shall serve him and cling to his Law.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="6">And that prophet or that dreamer
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             of dreams shall be put to death, because he has spoken words of
                            contradiction
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             about the Lord, about your God who brought you out from the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             of Egypt and who redeemed you out of the reign of slaves,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="304r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             to make you go astray from the way which the Lord your God commanded
                            you to walk
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             in. So you shall remove the evil from among you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="7">If your brother, the son of your mother, or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             your son or your daughter or the wife of your bosom or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             your friend, who is like you, entices you secretly, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             “Let us go and serve other gods,” which you have not known, you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             and your fathers,</l>
                        <l n="8">From the gods of the people
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             who are all around you, near to you or far off
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             from you, from the one edge of the earth even to the other edge of the
                            earth,</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             You shall not want to consent to his enticement and you shall not
                            listen
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             to him, and your eye shall not pity him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             and you shall not regret or conceal his iniquity.</l>
                        <l n="10">But
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             you shall surely kill him. Your hand shall be first on him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             to put him to death, and the hand of all the people thereafter.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="11">And you shall stone him with stones, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             he shall die, because he has sought to make you go astray from the
                            service of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             your God who brought you out from the land of Egypt, from the reign of
                            slaves.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="12">And all Israel shall hear, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             they shall fear, and the shall not continue to do a bad thing
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             like this among you.</l>
                        <l n="13">If you hear in one
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             of your cities which the Lord your God has given you to dwell there
                            <milestone unit="page" n="304v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             anyone saying,</l>
                        <l n="14">“Certain men, worthless people, have gone out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             from among you and have made the inhabitants of their city go astray,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             saying, “Let us go and serve other gods,”
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             which you have not known:”</l>
                        <l n="15">And you shall make search and inquire,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and ask well, and, lo, the thing is true —
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             that abominable thing was done among you —</l>
                        <l n="16">You shall surely
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             strike the inhabitants of that city with the edge of the sword:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             you shall destroy it and all that is in it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             and its cattle with the edge of the sword.</l>
                        <l n="17">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             you shall gather all the goods of it to the middle of its street and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             you shall burn in fire the city and all its goods
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             entirely to the Lord your God, and it shall be an eternal
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             heap. It shall not be built again.</l>
                        <l n="18">And nothing
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of the devoted thing shall cling to your hand, so that the Lord may
                            turn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             from his furious anger and show you mercy. And he shall have mercy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             on you and multiply you as he has sworn to your fathers,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="19">If you listen to the voice of the Lord your God to keep
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             all his commandments which I command you today, to do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             what seems right in the eyes of the Lord your God.</l>
                    </ab>
